Pokemon.Name: Bulbasaur
Pokemon.Description: For some time after its birth, it grows by gaining nourishment from the seed on its back.

Pokemon.Name: Ivysaur
Pokemon.Description: When the bud on its back starts swelling, a sweet aroma wafts to indicate the flower's coming bloom.

Pokemon.Name: Venusaur
Pokemon.Description: After a rainy day, the flower on its back smells stronger. The scent attracts other Pokemon.

Pokemon.Name: Charmander
Pokemon.Description: The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If healthy, its tail burns intensely.

Pokemon.Name: Charmeleon
Pokemon.Description: In the rocky mountains where Charmeleon live, their fiery tails shine at night like stars.

Pokemon.Name: Charizard
Pokemon.Description: It is said that Charizard's fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.

Pokemon.Name: Squirtle
Pokemon.Description: It shelters itself in its shell, then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.

Pokemon.Name: Wartortle
Pokemon.Description: It is said to live 10,000 years. Its furry tail is popular as a symbol of longevity.

Pokemon.Name: Blastoise
Pokemon.Description: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.

Pokemon.Name: Caterpie
Pokemon.Description: It releases a stench from its red antenna to repel enemies. It grows by molting repeatedly.

Pokemon.Name: Metapod
Pokemon.Description: A steel-hard shell protects its tender body. It quietly endures hardships while awaiting evolution.

Pokemon.Name: Butterfree
Pokemon.Description: It loves the honey of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.

Pokemon.Name: Weedle
Pokemon.Description: It eats its weight in leaves every day. It fends off attackers with the needle on its head.

Pokemon.Name: Kakuna
Pokemon.Description: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.

Pokemon.Name: Beedrill
Pokemon.Description: Its best attack involves flying around at high speed, striking with poison needles, then flying off.

Pokemon.Name: Pidgey
Pokemon.Description: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.

Pokemon.Name: Pidgeotto
Pokemon.Description: It flies over its wide territory in search of prey, downing it with its highly developed claws.

Pokemon.Name: Pidgeot
Pokemon.Description: By flapping its wings with all its might, Pidgeot can make a gust of wind capable of bending tall trees.

Pokemon.Name: Rattata
Pokemon.Description: Cautious in the extreme, its hardy vitality lets it live in any kind of environment.

Pokemon.Name: Raticate
Pokemon.Description: It whittles its constantly growing fangs by gnawing on hard things. It can chew apart cinder walls.

Pokemon.Name: Spearow
Pokemon.Description: It flaps its small wings busily to fly. Using its beak, it searches in grass for prey.

Pokemon.Name: Fearow
Pokemon.Description: It has the stamina to fly all day on its broad wings. It fights by using its sharp beak.

Pokemon.Name: Ekans
Pokemon.Description: It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind.

Pokemon.Name: Arbok
Pokemon.Description: The pattern on its belly is for intimidation. It constricts foes while they are frozen in fear.

Pokemon.Name: Pikachu
Pokemon.Description: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.

Pokemon.Name: Raichu
Pokemon.Description: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.

Pokemon.Name: Sandshrew
Pokemon.Description: To protect itself from attackers, it curls up into a ball. It lives in arid regions with minimal rainfall.

Pokemon.Name: Sandslash
Pokemon.Description: It curls up, then rolls into foes with its back. Its sharp spines inflict severe damage.

Pokemon.Name: Nidoran F
Pokemon.Description: While it does not prefer to fight, even one drop of the poison it secretes from barbs can be fatal.

Pokemon.Name: Nidorina
Pokemon.Description: When it senses danger, it raises all the barbs on its body. These barbs grow slower than Nidorino's.

Pokemon.Name: Nidoqueen
Pokemon.Description: Its entire body is armored with hard scales. It will protect the young in its burrow with its life.

Pokemon.Name: Nidoran M
Pokemon.Description: It scans its surroundings by raising its ears out of the grass. Its toxic horn is for protection.

Pokemon.Name: Nidorino
Pokemon.Description: It has a violent disposition and stabs foes with its horn, which oozes poison upon impact.

Pokemon.Name: Nidoking
Pokemon.Description: One swing of its mighty tail can snap a telephone pole as if it were a matchstick.

Pokemon.Name: Clefairy
Pokemon.Description: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.

Pokemon.Name: Clefable
Pokemon.Description: It is very wary and rarely shows itself to people. Its ears can hear a pin drop over half a mile away.

Pokemon.Name: Vulpix
Pokemon.Description: It controls balls of fire. As it grows, its six tails split from their tips to make more tails.

Pokemon.Name: Ninetales
Pokemon.Description: Its nine tails are said to be imbued with a mystic power. It can live for a thousand years.

Pokemon.Name: Jigglypuff
Pokemon.Description: When it wavers its big, round eyes, it begins singing a lullaby that makes everyone drowsy.

Pokemon.Name: Wigglytuff
Pokemon.Description: Its fine fur feels sublime to the touch. It can expand its body by inhaling air.

Pokemon.Name: Zubat
Pokemon.Description: It checks its surroundings and location using reflections of the ultrasonic waves from its mouth.

Pokemon.Name: Golbat
Pokemon.Description: Its sharp fangs puncture the toughest of hides and have small holes for greedily sucking blood.

Pokemon.Name: Oddish
Pokemon.Description: It often plants its root feet in the ground during the day and sows seeds as it walks about at night.

Pokemon.Name: Gloom
Pokemon.Description: The honey it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious, it can curl noses more than a mile away.

Pokemon.Name: Vileplume
Pokemon.Description: Its petals are the largest in the world. As it walks, it scatters extremely allergenic pollen.

Pokemon.Name: Paras
Pokemon.Description: Mushrooms named tochukaso grow on its back. They grow along with the host Paras.

Pokemon.Name: Parasect
Pokemon.Description: A mushroom grown larger than the host's body controls Parasect. It scatters poisonous spores.

Pokemon.Name: Venonat
Pokemon.Description: Its big eyes are actually clusters of tiny eyes. At night, its kind is drawn by light.

Pokemon.Name: Venomoth
Pokemon.Description: It flutters its wings to scatter dustlike scales. The scales leach toxins if they contact skin.

Pokemon.Name: Diglett
Pokemon.Description: A Pokemon that lives underground. Because of its dark habitat, it is repelled by bright sunlight.

Pokemon.Name: Dugtrio
Pokemon.Description: Its three heads move alternately, driving it through tough soil to depths of over 60 miles.

Pokemon.Name: Meowth
Pokemon.Description: It is nocturnal in nature. If it spots something shiny, its eyes glitter brightly.

Pokemon.Name: Persian
Pokemon.Description: A very haughty Pokemon. Among fans, the size of the jewel in its forehead is a topic of much talk.

Pokemon.Name: Psyduck
Pokemon.Description: Overwhelmed by enigmatic abilities, it suffers a constant headache. It sometimes uses mysterious powers.

Pokemon.Name: Golduck
Pokemon.Description: It is seen swimming dynamically and elegantly using its well-developed limbs and flippers.

Pokemon.Name: Mankey
Pokemon.Description: It lives in treetop colonies. If one becomes enraged, the whole colony rampages for no reason.

Pokemon.Name: Primeape
Pokemon.Description: It grows angry if you see its eyes and gets angrier if you run. If you beat it, it gets even madder.

Pokemon.Name: Growlithe
Pokemon.Description: A Pokemon with a loyal nature. It will remain motionless until it is given an order by its Trainer.

Pokemon.Name: Arcanine
Pokemon.Description: Its proud and regal appearance has captured the hearts of people since long ago.

Pokemon.Name: Poliwag
Pokemon.Description: Its skin is so thin, its internal organs are visible. It has trouble walking on its newly grown feet.

Stage.Name: Poliwrath
Stage.Requirement: Water Stone / Politoed Holding Minimum King's Rock 35

Pokemon.Name: Poliwhirl
Pokemon.Description: The spiral pattern on its belly subtly undulates. Staring at it gradually causes drowsiness.

Stage.Name: Poliwrath
Stage.Requirement: Water Stone / Politoed Holding Minimum King's Rock 35

Pokemon.Name: Poliwrath
Pokemon.Description: With its extremely tough muscles, it can keep swimming in the Pacific Ocean without resting.

Pokemon.Name: Abra
Pokemon.Description: Using its psychic power is such a strain on its brain that it needs to sleep for 18 hours a day.

Pokemon.Name: Kadabra
Pokemon.Description: It stares at its silver spoon to focus its mind. It emits more alpha waves while doing so.

Pokemon.Name: Alakazam
Pokemon.Description: The spoons clutched in its hands are said to have been created by its psychic powers.

Pokemon.Name: Machop
Pokemon.Description: Though small in stature, it is powerful enough to easily heft and throw a number of Geodude at once.

Pokemon.Name: Machoke
Pokemon.Description: It happily carries heavy cargo to toughen up. It willingly does hard work for people.

Pokemon.Name: Machamp
Pokemon.Description: Its four muscled arms slam foes with powerful punches and chops at blinding speed.

Pokemon.Name: Bellsprout
Pokemon.Description: It prefers hot and humid environments. It is quick at capturing prey with its vines.

Pokemon.Name: Weepinbell
Pokemon.Description: A Pokemon that appears to be a plant. It captures unwary prey by dousing them with a toxic powder.

Pokemon.Name: Victreebel
Pokemon.Description: It pools in its mouth a fluid with a honeylike scent, which is really an acid that dissolves anything.

Pokemon.Name: Tentacool
Pokemon.Description: Because its body is almost entirely composed of water, it shrivels up if it is washed ashore.

Pokemon.Name: Tentacruel
Pokemon.Description: It extends its 80 tentacles to form an encircling poisonous net that is difficult to escape.

Pokemon.Name: Geodude
Pokemon.Description: At rest, it looks just like a rock. Carelessly stepping on it will make it swing its fists angrily.

Pokemon.Name: Graveler
Pokemon.Description: It rolls on mountain paths to move. Once it builds momentum, no Pokemon can stop it without difficulty.

Pokemon.Name: Golem
Pokemon.Description: Even dynamite can't harm its hard, boulderlike body. It sheds its hide just once a year.

Pokemon.Name: Ponyta
Pokemon.Description: As a newborn, it can barely stand. However, through galloping, its legs are made tougher and faster.

Pokemon.Name: Rapidash
Pokemon.Description: When at an all-out gallop, its blazing mane sparkles, enhancing its beautiful appearance.

Pokemon.Name: Slowpoke
Pokemon.Description: Although slow, it is skilled at fishing with its tail. It does not feel pain if its tail is bitten.

Stage.Name: Slowbro
Stage.Requirement: Minimum 35 / Slowking Holding Minimum King's Rock 35

Pokemon.Name: Slowbro
Pokemon.Description: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the Shellder on its tail bites down.

Pokemon.Name: Magnemite
Pokemon.Description: The faster the units at its sides rotate, the greater the magnetic force they generate.

Pokemon.Name: Magneton
Pokemon.Description: Many mysteriously appear when more sunspots dot the sun. They stop TV sets from displaying properly.

Pokemon.Name: Farfetch'd
Pokemon.Description: It can't live without the stalk it holds. That's why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.

Pokemon.Name: Doduo
Pokemon.Description: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.

Pokemon.Name: Dodrio
Pokemon.Description: When Doduo evolves into this odd breed, one of its heads splits into two. It runs at nearly 40 mph.

Pokemon.Name: Seel
Pokemon.Description: A Pokemon that lives on icebergs. It swims in the sea using the point on its head to break up ice.

Pokemon.Name: Dewgong
Pokemon.Description: In snow, the pure white coat covering its body obscures it from predators.

Pokemon.Name: Grimer
Pokemon.Description: It was born when sludge in a dirty stream was exposed to the moon's X-rays. It appears among filth.

Pokemon.Name: Muk
Pokemon.Description: A toxic fluid seeps from its body. The fluid instantly kills plants and trees on contact.

Pokemon.Name: Shellder
Pokemon.Description: It swims backward by opening and closing its two shells. Its large tongue is always kept hanging out.

Pokemon.Name: Cloyster
Pokemon.Description: It fights by keeping its shell tightly shut for protection and by shooting spikes to repel foes.

Pokemon.Name: Gastly
Pokemon.Description: Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.

Pokemon.Name: Haunter
Pokemon.Description: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.

Pokemon.Name: Gengar
Pokemon.Description: The leer that floats in darkness belongs to a Gengar delighting in casting curses on people.

Pokemon.Name: Onix
Pokemon.Description: It burrows through the ground at a speed of 50 mph while feeding on large boulders.

Pokemon.Name: Drowzee
Pokemon.Description: It can tell what people are dreaming by sniffing with its big nose. It loves fun dreams.

Pokemon.Name: Hypno
Pokemon.Description: Seeing its swinging pendulum can induce sleep in three seconds, even in someone who just woke up.

Pokemon.Name: Krabby
Pokemon.Description: It lives in burrows dug on sandy beaches. Its pincers fully grow back if they are broken in battle.

Pokemon.Name: Kingler
Pokemon.Description: The larger pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.

Pokemon.Name: Voltorb
Pokemon.Description: It looks just like a Poke Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on touch.

Pokemon.Name: Electrode
Pokemon.Description: It is known to drift on winds if it is bloated to bursting with stored electricity.

Pokemon.Name: Exeggcute
Pokemon.Description: Its six eggs converse using telepathy. They can quickly gather if they become separated.

Pokemon.Name: Exeggutor
Pokemon.Description: It is called "The Walking Jungle." If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.

Pokemon.Name: Cubone
Pokemon.Description: When it thinks of its dead mother, it cries. Its crying makes the skull it wears rattle hollowly.

Pokemon.Name: Marowak
Pokemon.Description: From its birth, this savage Pokemon constantly holds bones. It is skilled in using them as weapons.

Pokemon.Name: Hitmonlee
Pokemon.Description: Its legs can stretch double. First-time foes are startled by its extensible reach.

Pokemon.Name: Hitmonchan
Pokemon.Description: The arm-twisting punches it throws pulverize even concrete. It rests after three minutes of fighting.

Pokemon.Name: Lickitung
Pokemon.Description: When it extends its over-six-foot-long tongue, its tail quivers. There is a possibility they are connected.

Pokemon.Name: Koffing
Pokemon.Description: Lighter-than-air gases in its body keep it aloft. The gases not only smell, they are also explosive.

Pokemon.Name: Weezing
Pokemon.Description: It grows by feeding on gases released by garbage. Though very rare, triplets have been found.

Pokemon.Name: Rhyhorn
Pokemon.Description: Its powerful tackles can destroy anything. However, it is too slow witted to help people work.

Pokemon.Name: Rhydon
Pokemon.Description: Standing on its hind legs freed its forelegs and made it smarter. It is very forgetful, however.

Pokemon.Name: Chansey
Pokemon.Description: A kindly Pokemon that lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokemon or people.

Pokemon.Name: Tangela
Pokemon.Description: The blue vines shrouding its body are covered in a growth of fine hair. It is known to be ticklish.

Pokemon.Name: Kangaskhan
Pokemon.Description: It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets the baby out to play only when it feels safe.

Pokemon.Name: Horsea
Pokemon.Description: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits murky ink and flees.

Pokemon.Name: Seadra
Pokemon.Description: Its spines provide protection. Its fins and bones are prized as traditional medicine ingredients.

Pokemon.Name: Goldeen
Pokemon.Description: Though it appears very elegant when swimming with fins unfurled, it can jab powerfully with its horn.

Pokemon.Name: Seaking
Pokemon.Description: In autumn, its body becomes more fatty in preparing to propose to a mate. It takes on beautiful colors.

Pokemon.Name: Staryu
Pokemon.Description: If its body is torn, it can grow back if the red core remains. The core flashes at midnight.

Pokemon.Name: Starmie
Pokemon.Description: At the center of its body is a red core, which sends mysterious radio signals into the night sky.

Pokemon.Name: Mr. Mime
Pokemon.Description: It shapes an invisible wall in midair by minutely vibrating its fingertips to stop molecules in the air.

Pokemon.Name: Scyther
Pokemon.Description: The sharp scythes on its forearms become increasingly sharp by cutting through hard objects.

Pokemon.Name: Jynx
Pokemon.Description: Its cries sound like human speech. However, it is impossible to tell what it is trying to say.

Pokemon.Name: Electabuzz
Pokemon.Description: It windmills its arms to slightly boost its punches. Foes have been known to escape in the meantime.

Pokemon.Name: Magmar
Pokemon.Description: When it breathes deeply, heat waves form around its body, making it hard to see clearly.

Pokemon.Name: Pinsir
Pokemon.Description: It grips prey with its pincers until the prey is torn in half. What it can't tear, it tosses far.

Pokemon.Name: Tauros
Pokemon.Description: Once it takes aim at its foe, it makes a headlong charge. It is famous for its violent nature.

Pokemon.Name: Magikarp
Pokemon.Description: A Magikarp living for many years can leap a mountain using Splash. The move remains useless, though.

Pokemon.Name: Gyarados
Pokemon.Description: Once it begins to rampage, a Gyarados will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm.

Pokemon.Name: Lapras
Pokemon.Description: It loves crossing the sea with people and Pokemon on its back. It understands human speech.

Pokemon.Name: Ditto
Pokemon.Description: It has the ability to reconstitute its entire cellular structure to transform into whatever it sees.

Diet.string: Diet can change with its form

Pokemon.Name: Eevee
Pokemon.Description: Because its genetic makeup is irregular, it quickly changes its form due to a variety of causes.

Stage.Name: Vaporeon
Stage.Requirement: Water Stone / Jolteon Thunderstone / Flareon Fire Stone / Espeon Dawn Stone / Umbreon Dusk Stone / Leafeon Leaf Stone / Glaceon Shiny Stone

Pokemon.Name: Vaporeon
Pokemon.Description: Its cell composition is similar to water molecules. As a result, it can melt away into water.

Pokemon.Name: Jolteon
Pokemon.Description: If agitated, it uses electricity to straighten out its fur and launch it in small bunches.

Pokemon.Name: Flareon
Pokemon.Description: Inhaled air is heated in the flame sac in its body to an intense fire over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.

Pokemon.Name: Porygon
Pokemon.Description: A man-made Pokemon created using advanced scientific means. It can move freely in cyberspace.

Pokemon.Name: Omanyte
Pokemon.Description: A Pokemon that was resurrected from a fossil using modern science. It swam in ancient seas.

Pokemon.Name: Omastar
Pokemon.Description: It is thought that this Pokemon became extinct because its spiral shell grew too large.

Pokemon.Name: Kabuto
Pokemon.Description: It is thought to have inhabited beaches 300 million years ago. It is protected by a stiff shell.

Pokemon.Name: Kabutops
Pokemon.Description: It is thought that this Pokemon came onto land because its prey adapted to life on land.

Pokemon.Name: Aerodactyl
Pokemon.Description: A Pokemon that roamed the skies in the dinosaur era. Its teeth are like saw blades.

Pokemon.Name: Snorlax
Pokemon.Description: When its belly is full, it becomes too lethargic to even lift a finger, so it is safe to bounce on its belly.

Pokemon.Name: Dratini
Pokemon.Description: It is called the "Mirage Pokemon" because so few have seen it. Its shed skin has been found.

Pokemon.Name: Dragonair
Pokemon.Description: If its body takes on an aura, the weather changes instantly. It is said to live in seas and lakes.

Pokemon.Name: Dragonite
Pokemon.Description: It is said to make its home somewhere in the sea. It guides crews of shipwrecks to shore.

Pokemon.Name: Chikorita
Pokemon.Description: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.

Pokemon.Name: Bayleef
Pokemon.Description: The buds that ring its neck give off a spicy aroma that perks people up.

Pokemon.Name: Meganium
Pokemon.Description: Its breath has the fantastic ability to revive dead plants and flowers.

Pokemon.Name: Cyndaquil
Pokemon.Description: It has a timid nature. If it is startled, the flames on its back burn more vigorously.

Pokemon.Name: Quilava
Pokemon.Description: It intimidates foes with the heat of its flames. The fire burns more strongly when it readies to fight.

Pokemon.Name: Typhlosion
Pokemon.Description: It attacks using blasts of fire. It creates heat shimmers with intense fire to hide itself.

Pokemon.Name: Totodile
Pokemon.Description: It has the habit of biting anything with its developed jaws. Even its Trainer needs to be careful.

Pokemon.Name: Croconaw
Pokemon.Description: Once it bites down, it won't let go until it loses its fangs. New fangs quickly grow into place.

Pokemon.Name: Feraligatr
Pokemon.Description: It usually moves slowly, but it goes at blinding speed when it attacks and bites prey.

Pokemon.Name: Sentret
Pokemon.Description: It has a very nervous nature. It stands up high on its tail so it can scan wide areas.

Pokemon.Name: Furret
Pokemon.Description: The mother puts its offspring to sleep by curling up around them. It corners foes with speed.

Pokemon.Name: Hoothoot
Pokemon.Description: It marks time precisely. Some countries consider it to be a wise friend, versed in the world's ways.

Pokemon.Name: Noctowl
Pokemon.Description: Its eyes are specially developed to enable it to see clearly even in murky darkness and minimal light.

Pokemon.Name: Ledyba
Pokemon.Description: It is so timid, it can't move if it isn't with a swarm of others. It conveys its feelings with scent.

Pokemon.Name: Ledian
Pokemon.Description: It uses starlight as energy. When more stars appear at night, the patterns on its back grow larger.

Pokemon.Name: Spinarak
Pokemon.Description: It sets a trap by spinning a web with thin but strong silk. It waits motionlessly for prey to arrive.

Pokemon.Name: Ariados
Pokemon.Description: It attaches silk to its prey and sets it free. Later, it tracks the silk to the prey and its friends.

Pokemon.Name: Crobat
Pokemon.Description: The transformation of its legs into wings made it better at flying, but more clumsy at walking.

Pokemon.Name: Chinchou
Pokemon.Description: It discharges positive and negative electricity from its antenna tips to shock its foes.

Pokemon.Name: Lanturn
Pokemon.Description: Lanturn's light can shine up from great depths. It is nicknamed "The Deep-Sea Star."

Pokemon.Name: Pichu
Pokemon.Description: The electric sacs in its cheeks are small. If even a little electricity leaks, it becomes shocked.

Pokemon.Name: Cleffa
Pokemon.Description: It is often seen when shooting stars fill the night skies. It's said to arrive riding on a shooting star.

Pokemon.Name: Igglybuff
Pokemon.Description: It has a soft and bouncy body. Once it starts bouncing, it becomes impossible to stop.

Pokemon.Name: Togepi
Pokemon.Description: It transforms the kindness and joy of others into happiness, which it stores in its shell.

Pokemon.Name: Togetic
Pokemon.Description: To share its happiness, it flies around the world seeking kind-hearted people.

Pokemon.Name: Natu
Pokemon.Description: It picks food from cactus plants, deftly avoiding buds and spines. It seems to skip about to move.

Pokemon.Name: Xatu
Pokemon.Description: This odd Pokemon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun's movement all day.

Pokemon.Name: Mareep
Pokemon.Description: Its fluffy coat swells to double when static electricity builds up. Touching it can be shocking.

Pokemon.Name: Flaaffy
Pokemon.Description: If its coat becomes fully charged with electricity, its tail lights up. It fires hair that zaps on impact.

Pokemon.Name: Ampharos
Pokemon.Description: The tip of its tail shines brightly. In the olden days, people sent signals using the tail's light.

Pokemon.Name: Bellossom
Pokemon.Description: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.

Pokemon.Name: Marill
Pokemon.Description: The oil-filled end of its tail floats on water. It keeps Marill from drowning even in a strong current.

Pokemon.Name: Azumarill
Pokemon.Description: It can spend all day in water, since it can inhale and store a large volume of air.

Pokemon.Name: Sudowoodo
Pokemon.Description: To avoid being attacked, it does nothing but mimic a tree. It hates water and flees from rain.

Pokemon.Name: Politoed
Pokemon.Description: It gathers groups of others as their leader. Its cries make Poliwag obey.

Pokemon.Name: Hoppip
Pokemon.Description: It drifts on winds. It is said that when Hoppip gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.

Pokemon.Name: Skiploom
Pokemon.Description: It blooms when the weather warms. It floats in the sky to soak up as much sunlight as possible.

Pokemon.Name: Jumpluff
Pokemon.Description: Blown by seasonal winds, it circles the globe, scattering cotton spores as it goes.

Pokemon.Name: Aipom
Pokemon.Description: It lives high among the treetops. It can use its tail as freely and cleverly as its hands.

Pokemon.Name: Sunkern
Pokemon.Description: It suddenly falls out of the sky in the morning. A year after a cold summer, their population explodes.

Pokemon.Name: Sunflora
Pokemon.Description: It gets energy from warm sunlight and is known for its habit of moving in pursuit of it.

Pokemon.Name: Yanma
Pokemon.Description: It can hover in one spot by flapping its wings at high speed. It flits about to guard its territory.

Pokemon.Name: Wooper
Pokemon.Description: When walking on land, it covers its body with a poisonous film that keeps its skin from dehydrating.

Pokemon.Name: Quagsire
Pokemon.Description: It has an easygoing nature. It doesn't care if it bumps its head on boats and boulders while swimming.

Pokemon.Name: Espeon
Pokemon.Description: Its fur is so sensitive, it can sense minute shifts in the air and predict the weather.

Pokemon.Name: Umbreon
Pokemon.Description: When exposed to the moon's aura, the rings on its body glow faintly and it gains a mysterious power.

Pokemon.Name: Murkrow
Pokemon.Description: If spotted, it will lure an unwary person into chasing it, then lose the pursuer on mountain trails.

Pokemon.Name: Slowking
Pokemon.Description: Being bitten by Shellder gave it intelligence comparable to that of award-winning scientists.

Pokemon.Name: Misdreavus
Pokemon.Description: A Pokemon that startles people in the middle of the night. It gathers fear as its energy.

Pokemon.Name: Unown
Pokemon.Description: When alone, nothing happens. However, if there are two or more, an odd power is said to emerge.

Pokemon.Name: Wobbuffet
Pokemon.Description: It desperately tries to keep its black tail hidden. It is said to be proof the tail hides a secret.

Pokemon.Name: Girafarig
Pokemon.Description: The head on its tail contains a small brain. It can instinctively fight even while facing backward.

Pokemon.Name: Pineco
Pokemon.Description: It looks just like a pinecone. Its shell protects it from bird Pokemon that peck it by mistake.

Pokemon.Name: Forretress
Pokemon.Description: It is encased in a steel shell. Its peering eyes are all that can be seen of its mysterious innards.

Pokemon.Name: Dunsparce
Pokemon.Description: It digs into the ground with its tail and makes a mazelike nest. It can fly just a little.

Pokemon.Name: Gligar
Pokemon.Description: It glides as if sliding. It startles foes by clamping on to their faces, then jabs with its poison stinger.

Pokemon.Name: Steelix
Pokemon.Description: It is thought its body transformed as a result of iron accumulating internally from swallowing soil.

Pokemon.Name: Snubbull
Pokemon.Description: Small Pokemon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by women to be cute.

Pokemon.Name: Granbull
Pokemon.Description: It is timid in spite of its looks. If it becomes enraged, however, it will strike with its huge fangs.

Pokemon.Name: Qwilfish
Pokemon.Description: It shoots the poison spines on its body in all directions. Its round form makes it a poor swimmer.

Pokemon.Name: Scizor
Pokemon.Description: It raises its pincers with eyelike markings for intimidation. It also swings them down dangerously.

Pokemon.Name: Shuckle
Pokemon.Description: It stores berries in its shell. The berries eventually ferment to become delicious juices.

Pokemon.Name: Heracross
Pokemon.Description: It loves sweet honey. To keep all the honey to itself, it hurls rivals away with its prized horn.

Pokemon.Name: Sneasel
Pokemon.Description: A smart and sneaky Pokemon. A pair may work together to steal eggs by having one lure the parents away.

Pokemon.Name: Teddiursa
Pokemon.Description: It lets honey soak into its paws so it can lick them all the time. Every set of paws tastes unique.

Pokemon.Name: Ursaring
Pokemon.Description: In its territory, it leaves scratches on trees that bear delicious berries or fruits.

Pokemon.Name: Slugma
Pokemon.Description: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn't keep moving, its body will cool and harden.

Pokemon.Name: Magcargo
Pokemon.Description: Its body temperature is roughly 18,000 degrees F. Flames spout from gaps in its hardened shell.

Pokemon.Name: Swinub
Pokemon.Description: It has a very sensitive nose. It can locate mushrooms, berries, and even hot springs buried under ice.

Pokemon.Name: Piloswine
Pokemon.Description: Covered by a shaggy coat, it is strong against the cold. Its tusks of ice thicken when it snows.

Pokemon.Name: Corsola
Pokemon.Description: Many live in the clean seas of the south. They apparently can't live in polluted waters.

Pokemon.Name: Remoraid
Pokemon.Description: It forcefully squirts water. The water jet never misses prey even if the Remoraid is deep in the sea.

Pokemon.Name: Octillery
Pokemon.Description: It loves to lurk inside holes in rocks. It sometimes sprays ink on prey by sticking out only its mouth.

Pokemon.Name: Delibird
Pokemon.Description: It carries food rolled up in its tail. It has the habit of sharing food with people lost in mountains.

Pokemon.Name: Mantine
Pokemon.Description: While elegantly swimming in the sea, it ignores Remoraid that cling to its fins seeking food scraps.

Pokemon.Name: Skarmory
Pokemon.Description: Despite being clad entirely in iron-hard armor, it flies at speeds over 180 mph.

Pokemon.Name: Houndour
Pokemon.Description: It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.

Pokemon.Name: Houndoom
Pokemon.Description: The flames it breathes when angry contain toxins. If they cause a burn, it will hurt forever.

Pokemon.Name: Kingdra
Pokemon.Description: It lives in caves on the seafloor and creates giant whirlpools every time it moves.

Pokemon.Name: Phanpy
Pokemon.Description: It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.

Pokemon.Name: Donphan
Pokemon.Description: It attacks by curling up, then rolling into its foe. It can blow apart a house in one hit.

Pokemon.Name: Porygon2
Pokemon.Description: It was upgraded to enable the exploration of other planets. However, it failed to measure up.

Pokemon.Name: Stantler
Pokemon.Description: Staring at its antlers creates an odd sensation as if one were being drawn into their centers.

Pokemon.Name: Smeargle
Pokemon.Description: It marks its territory by using its tail like a paintbrush. There are more than 5,000 different marks.

Pokemon.Name: Tyrogue
Pokemon.Description: It is famous for its eagerness to fight and always nurses injuries from challenging larger foes.

Stage.Name: Hitmonchan
Stage.Requirement: Superior Defense Minimum 20 / Hitmonlee Superior Attack Minimum 20 / Hitmontop Equal Attack and Defense

Pokemon.Name: Hitmontop
Pokemon.Description: It fights while spinning like a top. The centrifugal force boosts its destructive power by ten.

Pokemon.Name: Smoochum
Pokemon.Description: It tests everything by touching with its lips, which remember what it likes and dislikes.

Pokemon.Name: Elekid
Pokemon.Description: A weak electric current flows between its horns. Sticking a hand there shocks the unwary.

Pokemon.Name: Magby
Pokemon.Description: Its magma-like blood circulates throughout its body. Its body's heat can top 1,100 degrees F.

Pokemon.Name: Miltank
Pokemon.Description: It is said that kids who drink Miltank's milk grow up to become hearty, healthy adults.

Pokemon.Name: Blissey
Pokemon.Description: The eggs it lays are filled with happiness. Eating even one bite will bring a smile to anyone.

Pokemon.Name: Larvitar
Pokemon.Description: A Pokemon that eats soil. Once it has eaten a large mountain, it goes to sleep so it can grow.

Pokemon.Name: Pupitar
Pokemon.Description: Its body is as hard as bedrock. By venting pressurized gas, it can launch itself like a rocket.

Pokemon.Name: Tyranitar
Pokemon.Description: If it rampages, it knocks down mountains and buries rivers. Maps must be redrawn afterward.

Pokemon.Name: Treecko
Pokemon.Description: The soles of its feet are covered by countless tiny spikes, enabling it to walk on walls and ceilings.

Pokemon.Name: Grovyle
Pokemon.Description: It lives in dense jungles. While closing in on its prey, it leaps from branch to branch.

Pokemon.Name: Sceptile
Pokemon.Description: The leaves that grow on its arms can slice down thick trees. It is without peer in jungle combat.

Pokemon.Name: Torchic
Pokemon.Description: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees F.

Pokemon.Name: Combusken
Pokemon.Description: Its kicking mastery lets it loose 10 kicks per second. It emits sharp cries to intimidate foes.

Pokemon.Name: Blaziken
Pokemon.Description: Flames spout from its wrists, enveloping its knuckles. Its punches scorch its foes.

Pokemon.Name: Mudkip
Pokemon.Description: To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to heft boulders.

Pokemon.Name: Marshtomp
Pokemon.Description: Its sturdy legs give it sure footing, even in mud. It burrows into dirt to sleep.

Pokemon.Name: Swampert
Pokemon.Description: It can swim while towing a large ship. It bashes down foes with a swing of its thick arms.

Pokemon.Name: Poochyena
Pokemon.Description: A Pokemon with a persistent nature, it chases its chosen prey until the prey becomes exhausted.

Pokemon.Name: Mightyena
Pokemon.Description: It chases down prey in a pack. It will never disobey the commands of a skilled Trainer.

Pokemon.Name: Zigzagoon
Pokemon.Description: It walks in zigzag fashion. It is good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.

Pokemon.Name: Linoone
Pokemon.Description: It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.

Pokemon.Name: Wurmple
Pokemon.Description: Often targeted by bird Pokemon, it desperately resists by releasing poison from its tail spikes.

Pokemon.Name: Silcoon
Pokemon.Description: It wraps silk around the branches of a tree. It drinks rainwater on its silk while awaiting evolution.

Pokemon.Name: Beautifly
Pokemon.Description: Despite its looks, it is aggressive. It jabs with its long, thin mouth if disturbed while collecting pollen.

Pokemon.Name: Cascoon
Pokemon.Description: It never forgets any attack it endured while in the cocoon. After evolution, it seeks payback.

Pokemon.Name: Dustox
Pokemon.Description: Toxic powder is scattered with each flap. At night, it is known to strip leaves off trees lining boulevards.

Pokemon.Name: Lotad
Pokemon.Description: It looks like an aquatic plant and serves as a ferry to Pokemon that can't swim.

Pokemon.Name: Lombre
Pokemon.Description: It has a mischievous spirit. If it spots an angler, it will tug on the fishing line to interfere.

Pokemon.Name: Ludicolo
Pokemon.Description: If it hears festive music, all its muscles fill with energy. It can't help breaking out into a dance.

Pokemon.Name: Seedot
Pokemon.Description: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokemon.

Pokemon.Name: Nuzleaf
Pokemon.Description: The sound of its grass flute makes its listeners uneasy. It lives deep in forests.

Pokemon.Name: Shiftry
Pokemon.Description: By flapping its leafy fan, it can whip up gusts of 100 ft/second that can level houses.

Pokemon.Name: Taillow
Pokemon.Description: It has a gutsy spirit that makes it bravely take on tough foes. It flies in search of warm climates.

Pokemon.Name: Swellow
Pokemon.Description: It circles the sky in search of prey. When it spots one, it dives steeply to catch the prey.

Pokemon.Name: Wingull
Pokemon.Description: It soars high in the sky, riding on updrafts like a glider. It carries food tucked in its bill.

Pokemon.Name: Pelipper
Pokemon.Description: It is a messenger of the skies, carrying small Pokemon and eggs to safety in its bill.

Pokemon.Name: Ralts
Pokemon.Description: If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokemon, its body warms up slightly.

Pokemon.Name: Kirlia
Pokemon.Description: If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.

Pokemon.Name: Gardevoir
Pokemon.Description: To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.

Pokemon.Name: Surskit
Pokemon.Description: It appears as if it is skating on water. It draws prey with a sweet scent from the tip of its head.

Pokemon.Name: Masquerain
Pokemon.Description: Its antennae have eye patterns on them. Its four wings enable it to hover and fly in any direction.

Pokemon.Name: Shroomish
Pokemon.Description: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.

Pokemon.Name: Breloom
Pokemon.Description: Its short arms stretch when it throws punches. Its technique is equal to that of pro boxers.

Pokemon.Name: Slakoth
Pokemon.Description: It spends nearly all its time in a day sprawled out. Just seeing it makes one drowsy.

Pokemon.Name: Vigoroth
Pokemon.Description: Its heart beats at a tenfold tempo, so it cannot sit still for even a moment.

Pokemon.Name: Slaking
Pokemon.Description: The world's laziest Pokemon. When it is lounging, it is actually saving energy for striking back.

Pokemon.Name: Nincada
Pokemon.Description: It grows underground, sensing its surroundings using antennae instead of its virtually blind eyes.

Pokemon.Name: Ninjask
Pokemon.Description: Because it moves so quickly, it sometimes becomes unseeable. It congregates around tree sap.

Pokemon.Name: Shedinja
Pokemon.Description: A discarded bug shell that came to life. Peering into the crack on its back is said to steal one's spirit.

Pokemon.Name: Whismur
Pokemon.Description: Usually, its cries are like quiet murmurs. If frightened, it shrieks at the same volume as a jet plane.

Pokemon.Name: Loudred
Pokemon.Description: The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.

Pokemon.Name: Exploud
Pokemon.Description: Its howls can be heard over six miles away. It emits all sorts of noises from the ports on its body.

Pokemon.Name: Makuhita
Pokemon.Description: It toughens its body by slamming into thick trees. Many snapped trees can be found near its nest.

Pokemon.Name: Hariyama
Pokemon.Description: It loves to match power with big-bodied Pokemon. It can knock a truck flying with its arm thrusts.

Pokemon.Name: Azurill
Pokemon.Description: Its tail bounces like a rubber ball. It flings that tail around to fight opponents bigger than itself.

Pokemon.Name: Nosepass
Pokemon.Description: When endangered, it may protect itself by raising its magnetism and drawing iron objects to its body.

Pokemon.Name: Skitty
Pokemon.Description: It can't stop itself from chasing moving things, and it runs in a circle, chasing its own tail.

Pokemon.Name: Delcatty
Pokemon.Description: It is highly popular among female Trainers for its sublime fur. It does not keep a nest.

Pokemon.Name: Sableye
Pokemon.Description: It hides in the darkness of caves. Its diet of gems has transformed its eyes into gemstones.

Pokemon.Name: Mawile
Pokemon.Description: Attached to its head is a huge set of jaws formed by horns. It can chew through iron beams.

Pokemon.Name: Aron
Pokemon.Description: It usually lives deep in mountains. However, hunger may drive it to eat railroad tracks and cars.

Pokemon.Name: Lairon
Pokemon.Description: For food, it digs up iron ore. It smashes its steely body against others to fight over territory.

Pokemon.Name: Aggron
Pokemon.Description: While seeking iron for food, it digs tunnels by breaking through bedrock with its steel horns.

Pokemon.Name: Meditite
Pokemon.Description: It always trains deep in mountains. It levitates when it heightens its spiritual power through meditation.

Pokemon.Name: Medicham
Pokemon.Description: It gains the ability to see the aura of its opponents by honing its mind through starvation.

Pokemon.Name: Electrike
Pokemon.Description: Using electricity stored in its fur, it stimulates its muscles to heighten its reaction speed.

Pokemon.Name: Manectric
Pokemon.Description: It discharges electricity from its mane. It creates a thundercloud overhead to drop lightning bolts.

Pokemon.Name: Plusle
Pokemon.Description: It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.

Pokemon.Name: Minun
Pokemon.Description: It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.

Pokemon.Name: Volbeat
Pokemon.Description: It communicates with others by lighting up its rear at night. It loves Illumise's sweet aroma.

Pokemon.Name: Illumise
Pokemon.Description: With its sweet aroma, it guides Volbeat to draw signs with light in the night sky.

Pokemon.Name: Roselia
Pokemon.Description: The more healthy the Roselia, the more pleasant its flowers' aroma. Its scent deeply relaxes people.

Pokemon.Name: Gulpin
Pokemon.Description: Almost all its body is its stomach. Its harsh digestive juices quickly dissolve anything it swallows.

Pokemon.Name: Swalot
Pokemon.Description: It swallows anything whole. It sweats toxic fluids from its follicles to douse foes.

Pokemon.Name: Carvanha
Pokemon.Description: They swarm any foe that invades their territory. Their sharp fangs can tear out boat hulls.

Pokemon.Name: Sharpedo
Pokemon.Description: Its fangs rip through sheet iron. It swims at 75 mph and is known as "The Bully of the Sea."

Pokemon.Name: Wailmer
Pokemon.Description: On sunny days, it lands on beaches to bounce like a ball and play. It spouts water from its nose.

Pokemon.Name: Wailord
Pokemon.Description: The biggest of all Pokemon. It can dive to a depth of almost 10,000 feet on only one breath.

Pokemon.Name: Numel
Pokemon.Description: Its humped back stores intensely hot magma. In rain, the magma cools, slowing its movement.

Pokemon.Name: Camerupt
Pokemon.Description: It has volcanoes on its back. If magma builds up in its body, it shudders, then erupts violently.

Pokemon.Name: Torkoal
Pokemon.Description: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.

Pokemon.Name: Spoink
Pokemon.Description: It bounces constantly, using its tail like a spring. The shock of bouncing keeps its heart beating.

Pokemon.Name: Grumpig
Pokemon.Description: It uses black pearls to amplify its psycho-power. It does an odd dance to gain control over foes.

Pokemon.Name: Spinda
Pokemon.Description: No two Spinda have the same pattern of spots. Its tottering step fouls the aim of foes.

Pokemon.Name: Trapinch
Pokemon.Description: It makes a conical pit in desert sand and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.

Pokemon.Name: Vibrava
Pokemon.Description: It violently shudders its wings, generating ultrasonic waves to induce headaches in people.

Pokemon.Name: Flygon
Pokemon.Description: It whips up sandstorms with powerful flaps of its wings. It is known as "The Desert Spirit."

Pokemon.Name: Cacnea
Pokemon.Description: By storing water in its body, this desert dweller can survive for 30 days without water.

Pokemon.Name: Cacturne
Pokemon.Description: It becomes active at night, seeking prey that is exhausted from the day's desert heat.

Pokemon.Name: Swablu
Pokemon.Description: It can't relax if it or its surroundings are not clean. It wipes off dirt with its wings.

Pokemon.Name: Altaria
Pokemon.Description: If it bonds with a person, it will gently envelop the friend with its soft wings, then hum.

Pokemon.Name: Zangoose
Pokemon.Description: It has feuded with Seviper for many generations. Its sharp claws are its biggest weapons.

Pokemon.Name: Seviper
Pokemon.Description: For many generations, it has feuded with Zangoose. It whets its bladed tail on rocks for battle.

Pokemon.Name: Lunatone
Pokemon.Description: Because it turns active on nights of the full moon, it is said to have some link to the lunar phases.

Pokemon.Name: Solrock
Pokemon.Description: A new Pokemon species, rumored to be from the sun. It gives off light while spinning.

Pokemon.Name: Barboach
Pokemon.Description: Its slimy body is hard to grasp. In one region, it is said to have been born from hardened mud.

Pokemon.Name: Whiscash
Pokemon.Description: It is extremely protective of its territory. If any foe approaches, it attacks using vicious tremors.

Pokemon.Name: Corphish
Pokemon.Description: Its hardy vitality enables it to adapt to any environment. Its pincers will never release prey.

Pokemon.Name: Crawdaunt
Pokemon.Description: It is a ruffian that uses its pincers to pick up and toss out other Pokemon from its pond.

Pokemon.Name: Baltoy
Pokemon.Description: It moves by spinning on its foot. It is a rare Pokemon that was discovered in ancient ruins.

Pokemon.Name: Claydol
Pokemon.Description: An ancient clay figurine that came to life as a Pokemon from exposure to a mysterious ray of light.

Pokemon.Name: Lileep
Pokemon.Description: It lived on the seafloor 100 million years ago and was reanimated scientifically.

Pokemon.Name: Cradily
Pokemon.Description: It lives in the shallows of warm seas. When the tide goes out, it digs up prey from beaches.

Pokemon.Name: Anorith
Pokemon.Description: A Pokemon ancestor that was reanimated from a fossil. It lived in the sea and hunted with claws.

Pokemon.Name: Armaldo
Pokemon.Description: It went ashore after evolving. Its entire body is clad in a sturdy armor.

Pokemon.Name: Feebas
Pokemon.Description: It is a shabby and ugly Pokemon. However, it is very hardy and can survive on little water.

Pokemon.Name: Milotic
Pokemon.Description: Its lovely scales are described as rainbow colored. They change color depending on the viewing angle.

Pokemon.Name: Castform
Pokemon.Description: Its appearance changes with the weather. Recently, its molecules were found to be just like water.

Pokemon.Name: Kecleon
Pokemon.Description: It can freely change its body's color. The zigzag pattern on its belly doesn't change, however.

Pokemon.Name: Shuppet
Pokemon.Description: It loves vengeful emotions and hangs in rows under the eaves of houses where vengeful people live.

Pokemon.Name: Banette
Pokemon.Description: A doll that became a Pokemon over its grudge from being junked. It seeks the child that disowned it.

Pokemon.Name: Duskull
Pokemon.Description: It loves the crying of children. It startles bad kids by passing through walls and making them cry.

Pokemon.Name: Dusclops
Pokemon.Description: It seeks drifting will-o'-the-wisps and sucks them into its empty body. What happens inside is a mystery.

Pokemon.Name: Tropius
Pokemon.Description: Delicious fruits grew out from around its neck because it always ate the same kind of fruit.

Pokemon.Name: Chimecho
Pokemon.Description: Its cries echo inside its hollow body to emerge as beautiful notes for startling and repelling foes.

Pokemon.Name: Absol
Pokemon.Description: Rumored to sense disasters with its horn, it became a target. It fled deep into the mountains.

Pokemon.Name: Wynaut
Pokemon.Description: It grows strong by pushing up against others en masse. It loves eating sweet fruit.

Pokemon.Name: Snorunt
Pokemon.Description: It is said that several Snorunt gather under giant leaves and live together in harmony.

Pokemon.Name: Glalie
Pokemon.Description: It prevents prey from escaping by instantaneously freezing moisture in the air.

Pokemon.Name: Spheal
Pokemon.Description: It rolls across ice floes to reach shore because its body is poorly shaped for swimming.

Pokemon.Name: Sealeo
Pokemon.Description: It habitually spins things on its nose. By doing so, it learns textures and odors.

Pokemon.Name: Walrein
Pokemon.Description: It shatters ice with its big tusks. Its thick blubber repels not only the cold, but also enemy attacks.

Pokemon.Name: Clamperl
Pokemon.Description: It makes a single pearl during its lifetime. The pearl is said to amplify psychic power.

Stage.Name: Huntail
Stage.Requirement: Holding Minimum Deepseatooth 20 / Gorebyss Holding Minimum Deepseascale

Pokemon.Name: Huntail
Pokemon.Description: It lives deep in the sea. With a tail shaped like a small fish, it attracts unsuspecting prey.

Pokemon.Name: Gorebyss
Pokemon.Description: It lives at the bottom of the sea. In the springtime, its pink body turns more vivid for some reason.

Pokemon.Name: Relicanth
Pokemon.Description: A rare Pokemon discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.

Pokemon.Name: Luvdisc
Pokemon.Description: It lives in warm seas. It is said that a couple finding this Pokemon will be blessed with eternal love.

Pokemon.Name: Bagon
Pokemon.Description: Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping off cliffs every day.

Pokemon.Name: Shelgon
Pokemon.Description: Within its rugged shell, its cells have begun changing. The shell peels off the instant it evolves.

Pokemon.Name: Salamence
Pokemon.Description: As a result of its long-held dream of flying, its cellular structure changed, and wings grew out.

Pokemon.Name: Beldum
Pokemon.Description: It converses with others by using magnetic pulses. In a swarm, they move in perfect unison.

Pokemon.Name: Metang
Pokemon.Description: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its steel body won't be scratched if it collides with a jet.

Pokemon.Name: Metagross
Pokemon.Description: Metang combined to form it. With four brains, it has the intelligence of a supercomputer.

Pokemon.Name: Turtwig
Pokemon.Description: The shell on its back is made of soil. On a very healthy Turtwig, the shell should feel moist.

Pokemon.Name: Grotle
Pokemon.Description: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokemon there on its back.

Pokemon.Name: Torterra
Pokemon.Description: Some Pokemon are born on a Torterra's back and spend their entire life there.

Pokemon.Name: Chimchar
Pokemon.Description: It is very agile. Before going to sleep, it extinguishes the flame on its tail to prevent fires.

Pokemon.Name: Monferno
Pokemon.Description: It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.

Pokemon.Name: Infernape
Pokemon.Description: It uses unique fighting moves with fire on its hands and feet. It will take on any opponent.

Pokemon.Name: Piplup
Pokemon.Description: A poor walker, it often falls down. However, its strong pride makes it puff up its chest without a care.

Pokemon.Name: Prinplup
Pokemon.Description: Because every Prinplup considers itself to be the most important, they can never form a group.

Pokemon.Name: Empoleon
Pokemon.Description: If anyone were to hurt its pride, it would slash them with wings that can cleave through an ice floe.

Pokemon.Name: Starly
Pokemon.Description: Because they are weak individually, they form groups. However, they bicker if the group grows too big.

Pokemon.Name: Staravia
Pokemon.Description: Recognizing their own weakness, they always live in a group. When alone, a Staravia cries noisily.

Pokemon.Name: Staraptor
Pokemon.Description: It never stops attacking even if it is injured. It fusses over the shape of its comb.

Pokemon.Name: Bidoof
Pokemon.Description: A comparison revealed that Bidoof's front teeth grow at the same rate as Rattata's.

Pokemon.Name: Bibarel
Pokemon.Description: A river dammed by Bibarel will never overflow its banks, which is appreciated by people nearby.

Pokemon.Name: Kricketot
Pokemon.Description: Its legs are short. Whenever it stumbles, its stiff antennae clack with a xylophone-like sound.

Pokemon.Name: Kricketune
Pokemon.Description: There is a village that hosts a contest based on the amazingly variable cries of this Pokemon.

Pokemon.Name: Shinx
Pokemon.Description: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.

Pokemon.Name: Luxio
Pokemon.Description: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

Pokemon.Name: Luxray
Pokemon.Description: It can see clearly through walls to track down its prey and seek its lost young.

Pokemon.Name: Budew
Pokemon.Description: Sensitive to changing temperature, the bud is said to bloom when it feels the sun's warm touch.

Pokemon.Name: Roserade
Pokemon.Description: Each of its hands contains different toxins, but both hands can jab with near-fatal power.

Pokemon.Name: Cranidos
Pokemon.Description: A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million years ago, it would snap obstructing trees with head butts.

Pokemon.Name: Rampardos
Pokemon.Description: If two were to smash their heads together, their foot-thick skulls would keep them from fainting.

Pokemon.Name: Shieldon
Pokemon.Description: It is outstandingly armored. As a result, it can eat grass and berries without having to fight.

Pokemon.Name: Bastiodon
Pokemon.Description: When they lined up side by side, no foe could break through. They shielded their young in that way.

Pokemon.Name: Burmy Plant Forme
Pokemon.Description: Even if it is born where there are no cocooning materials, it somehow always ends up with a cloak.

Pokemon.Name: Burmy Sandy Forme
Pokemon.Description: Even if it is born where there are no cocooning materials, it somehow always ends up with a cloak.

Pokemon.Name: Burmy Trash Forme
Pokemon.Description: Even if it is born where there are no cocooning materials, it somehow always ends up with a cloak.

Pokemon.Name: Wormadam Plant Forme
Pokemon.Description: When evolving, its body takes in surrounding materials. As a result, there are many body variations.

Pokemon.Name: Wormadam Sandy Forme
Pokemon.Description: When evolving, its body takes in surrounding materials. As a result, there are many body variations.

Pokemon.Name: Wormadam Trash Forme
Pokemon.Description: When evolving, its body takes in surrounding materials. As a result, there are many body variations.

Pokemon.Name: Mothim
Pokemon.Description: While it loves floral honey, it won't gather any itself. Instead, it plots to steal some from Combee.

Pokemon.Name: Combee
Pokemon.Description: The trio is together from birth. It constantly gathers honey from flowers to please Vespiquen.

Pokemon.Name: Vespiquen
Pokemon.Description: It releases various pheromones to make the grubs in its body do its bidding while fighting foes.

Pokemon.Name: Pachirisu
Pokemon.Description: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

Pokemon.Name: Buizel
Pokemon.Description: It spins its two tails like a screw to propel itself through water. The tails also slice clinging seaweed.

Pokemon.Name: Floatzel
Pokemon.Description: It is a common sight around fishing ports. It is known to rescue people and carry off prey.

Pokemon.Name: Cherubi
Pokemon.Description: The small ball is not only filled with nutrients, it is also tasty. Starly try to peck it off.

Pokemon.Name: Cherrim
Pokemon.Description: If it senses strong sunlight, it opens its folded petals to absorb the sun's rays with its whole body.

Pokemon.Name: Shellos
Pokemon.Description: Beware of pushing strongly on its squishy body, as it makes a mysterious purple fluid ooze out.

Pokemon.Name: Gastrodon
Pokemon.Description: Long ago, its entire back was shielded with a sturdy shell. There are traces of it left in its cells.

Pokemon.Name: Ambipom
Pokemon.Description: Split into two, the tails are so adept at handling and doing things, Ambipom rarely uses its hands.

Pokemon.Name: Drifloon
Pokemon.Description: Because of the way it floats aimlessly, an old folktale calls it a "Signpost for Wandering Spirits."

Pokemon.Name: Drifblim
Pokemon.Description: At dusk, swarms of them are carried aloft on winds. When noticed, they suddenly vanish.

Pokemon.Name: Buneary
Pokemon.Description: Its ears are always rolled up. They can be forcefully extended to shatter even a large boulder.

Pokemon.Name: Lopunny
Pokemon.Description: The ears appear to be delicate. If they are touched roughly, it kicks with its graceful legs.

Pokemon.Name: Mismagius
Pokemon.Description: Its cry sounds like an incantation. It is said the cry may rarely be imbued with happiness-giving power.

Pokemon.Name: Honchkrow
Pokemon.Description: If one utters a deep cry, many Murkrow gather quickly. For this, it is called "Summoner of Night."

Pokemon.Name: Glameow
Pokemon.Description: It hides its spiteful tendency of hooking its claws into the nose of its Trainer if it isn't fed.

Pokemon.Name: Purugly
Pokemon.Description: It binds its body with its tails to make itself look bigger. If it locks eyes, it will glare ceaselessly.

Pokemon.Name: Chingling
Pokemon.Description: There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops, the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.

Pokemon.Name: Stunky
Pokemon.Description: It sprays a foul fluid from its rear. Its stench spreads over a mile radius, driving Pokemon away.

Pokemon.Name: Skuntank
Pokemon.Description: It attacks by spraying a horribly smelly fluid from the tip of its tail. Attacks from above confound it.

Pokemon.Name: Bronzor
Pokemon.Description: There are researchers who believe this Pokemon reflected like a mirror in the distant past.

Pokemon.Name: Bronzong
Pokemon.Description: It brought rains by opening portals to another world. It was revered as a bringer of plentiful harvests.

Pokemon.Name: Bonsly
Pokemon.Description: It prefers an arid atmosphere. It leaks water that looks like tears when adjusting its moisture level.

Pokemon.Name: Mime Jr.
Pokemon.Description: It mimics the expressions and motions of those it sees to understand the feelings of others.

Pokemon.Name: Happiny
Pokemon.Description: It likes to carry around a small rock. It may wander around others' feet and cause them to stumble.

Pokemon.Name: Chatot
Pokemon.Description: Its tongue is just like a human's. As a result, it can cleverly mimic human speech.

Pokemon.Name: Spiritomb
Pokemon.Description: Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.

Pokemon.Name: Gible
Pokemon.Description: It attacks using its huge mouth. While its attacks are powerful, it hurts itself out of clumsiness, too.

Pokemon.Name: Gabite
Pokemon.Description: It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.

Pokemon.Name: Garchomp
Pokemon.Description: It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.

Pokemon.Name: Munchlax
Pokemon.Description: In its desperation to gulp down food, it forgets about the food it has hidden under its fur.

Pokemon.Name: Riolu
Pokemon.Description: It has the peculiar power of being able to see emotions such as joy and rage in the form of waves.

Pokemon.Name: Lucario
Pokemon.Description: A well-trained one can sense auras to identify and take in the feelings of creatures over half a mile away.

Pokemon.Name: Hippopotas
Pokemon.Description: It shuts its nostrils tight then travels through sand as if walking. They form colonies of around ten.

Pokemon.Name: Hippowdon
Pokemon.Description: It is surprisingly quick to anger. It holds its mouth agape as a display of its strength.

Pokemon.Name: Skorupi
Pokemon.Description: As soon as the tail claws close, its needle tips secrete poison. It can survive a year without food.

Pokemon.Name: Drapion
Pokemon.Description: Possessing a sturdy build, it takes pride in its strength, taking down foes without using toxins.

Pokemon.Name: Croagunk
Pokemon.Description: It rarely fights fairly, but that is strictly to ensure survival. It is popular as a mascot.

Pokemon.Name: Toxicroak
Pokemon.Description: It has a poison sac at its throat. When it croaks, the stored poison is churned for greater potency.

Pokemon.Name: Carnivine
Pokemon.Description: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

Pokemon.Name: Finneon
Pokemon.Description: The line running down its side can store sunlight. It shines vividly at night.

Pokemon.Name: Lumineon
Pokemon.Description: It crawls along the seafloor using its long front fins like legs. It competes for food with Lanturn.

Pokemon.Name: Mantyke
Pokemon.Description: People organize tours to see this Pokemon frolic and skim the tops of waves with Remoraid.

Pokemon.Name: Snover
Pokemon.Description: Seemingly curious about people, they gather around footsteps they find on snowy mountains.

Pokemon.Name: Abomasnow
Pokemon.Description: They appear when the snow flowers bloom. When the petals fall, they retreat to places unknown again.

Pokemon.Name: Weavile
Pokemon.Description: Evolution made it even more devious. It communicates by clawing signs in boulders.

Pokemon.Name: Magnezone
Pokemon.Description: A group tried to use scientific means to make Magnezone evolve, but their efforts ended in failure.

Pokemon.Name: Lickilicky
Pokemon.Description: The long tongue is always soggy with slobber. The saliva contains a solvent that causes numbness.

Pokemon.Name: Rhyperior
Pokemon.Description: It can launch a rock held in its hand like a missile by tightening then expanding muscles instantly.

Pokemon.Name: Tangrowth
Pokemon.Description: Its arms are made of plants that bind themselves to things. They grow back right away if cut.

Pokemon.Name: Electivire
Pokemon.Description: Heedless of enemy attacks, it closes in, shoves its tails onto the foe, then looses high voltage.

Pokemon.Name: Magmortar
Pokemon.Description: When launching 3,600 degrees F fireballs, its body takes on a whitish hue from the intense heat.

Pokemon.Name: Togekiss
Pokemon.Description: It shares many blessings with people who respect one another's rights and avoid needless strife.

Pokemon.Name: Yanmega
Pokemon.Description: Its jaw power is incredible. It is adept at biting apart foes while flying by at high speed.

Pokemon.Name: Leafeon
Pokemon.Description: It basically does not fight. With cells similar to those of plants, it can perform photosynthesis.

Pokemon.Name: Glaceon
Pokemon.Description: By controlling its body heat, it can freeze the atmosphere around it to make a diamond-dust flurry.

Pokemon.Name: Gliscor
Pokemon.Description: If it succeeds in catching even a faint breeze properly, it can circle the globe without flapping once.

Pokemon.Name: Mamoswine
Pokemon.Description: A frozen one was dug up from soil dating back 10,000 years. It woke up to much amazement.

Pokemon.Name: Porygon-Z
Pokemon.Description: Its programming was modified to enable work in alien dimensions. It did not work as planned.

Pokemon.Name: Gallade
Pokemon.Description: When trying to protect someone, it extends its elbows as if they were swords and fights savagely.

Pokemon.Name: Probopass
Pokemon.Description: It freely controls three small units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.

Pokemon.Name: Dusknoir
Pokemon.Description: It is said to take lost spirits into its pliant body and guide them home.

Pokemon.Name: Froslass
Pokemon.Description: It freezes prey by blowing its -58 degrees F breath. It is said to then secretly display its prey.

Pokemon.Name: Snivy
Pokemon.Description: It is very intelligent and calm. Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.

Pokemon.Name: Servine
Pokemon.Description: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.

Pokemon.Name: Serperior
Pokemon.Description: It can stop its opponents' movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.

Pokemon.Name: Tepig
Pokemon.Description: It can deftly dodge its foe's attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.

Pokemon.Name: Pignite
Pokemon.Description: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

Pokemon.Name: Emboar
Pokemon.Description: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.

Pokemon.Name: Oshawott
Pokemon.Description: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

Pokemon.Name: Dewott
Pokemon.Description: Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.

Pokemon.Name: Samurott
Pokemon.Description: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.

Pokemon.Name: Patrat
Pokemon.Description: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.

Pokemon.Name: Watchog
Pokemon.Description: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

Pokemon.Name: Lillipup
Pokemon.Description: It faces strong opponents with great courage. But, when at a disadvantage in a fight, this intelligent Pokemon flees.

Pokemon.Name: Herdier
Pokemon.Description: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

Pokemon.Name: Stoutland
Pokemon.Description: It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. Its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.

Pokemon.Name: Purrloin
Pokemon.Description: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can't help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

Pokemon.Name: Liepard
Pokemon.Description: These Pokemon vanish and appear unexpectedly. Many Trainers are drawn to their beautiful form and fur.

Pokemon.Name: Pansage
Pokemon.Description: This Pokemon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.

Pokemon.Name: Simisage
Pokemon.Description: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

Pokemon.Name: Pansear
Pokemon.Description: When it is angered, the temperature of its head tuft reaches 600 F. It uses its tuft to roast berries.

Pokemon.Name: Simisear
Pokemon.Description: It loves sweets because they become energy for the fire burning inside its body.

Pokemon.Name: Panpour
Pokemon.Description: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

Pokemon.Name: Simipour
Pokemon.Description: The tuft on its head holds water. When the level runs low, it replenishes the tuft by siphoning up water with its tail.

Pokemon.Name: Munna
Pokemon.Description: Munna always float in the air. People whose dreams are eaten by them forget what the dreams had been about.

Pokemon.Name: Musharna
Pokemon.Description: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokemon.

Pokemon.Name: Pidove
Pokemon.Description: Each follows its Trainer's orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.

Pokemon.Name: Tranquill
Pokemon.Description: It can return to its Trainer's location regardless of the distance separating them.

Pokemon.Name: Unfezant
Pokemon.Description: Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females' flying abilities surpass those of the males.

Pokemon.Name: Blitzle
Pokemon.Description: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use their flashing manes to communicate with one another.

Pokemon.Name: Zebstrika
Pokemon.Description: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

Pokemon.Name: Roggenrola
Pokemon.Description: Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressed underground, its body is as hard as steel.

Pokemon.Name: Boldore
Pokemon.Description: When it overflows with power, the orange crystal on its body glows. It looks for underground water in caves.

Pokemon.Name: Gigalith
Pokemon.Description: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.

Pokemon.Name: Woobat
Pokemon.Description: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.

Pokemon.Name: Swoobat
Pokemon.Description: It emits sound waves of various frequencies from its nose, including some powerful enough to destroy rocks.

Pokemon.Name: Drilbur
Pokemon.Description: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.

Pokemon.Name: Excadrill
Pokemon.Description: It can help in tunnel construction. Its drill has evolved into steel strong enough to bore through iron plates.

Pokemon.Name: Audino
Pokemon.Description: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

Pokemon.Name: Timburr
Pokemon.Description: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle the lumber without difficulty.

Pokemon.Name: Gurdurr
Pokemon.Description: This Pokemon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

Pokemon.Name: Conkeldurr
Pokemon.Description: It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.

Pokemon.Name: Tympole
Pokemon.Description: They warn others of danger by vibrating their cheeks to create a high-pitched sound.

Pokemon.Name: Palpitoad
Pokemon.Description: When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, they can make waves in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.

Pokemon.Name: Seismitoad
Pokemon.Description: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.

Pokemon.Name: Throh
Pokemon.Description: When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts.

Pokemon.Name: Sawk
Pokemon.Description: The sound of Sawk punching boulders and trees can be heard all the way from the mountains where they train.

Pokemon.Name: Sewaddle
Pokemon.Description: Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.

Pokemon.Name: Swadloon
Pokemon.Description: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

Pokemon.Name: Leavanny
Pokemon.Description: Upon finding a small Pokemon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.

Pokemon.Name: Venipede
Pokemon.Description: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokemon that try to prey on it.

Pokemon.Name: Whirlipede
Pokemon.Description: Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.

Pokemon.Name: Scolipede
Pokemon.Description: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

Pokemon.Name: Cottonee
Pokemon.Description: When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.

Pokemon.Name: Whimsicott
Pokemon.Description: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

Pokemon.Name: Petilil
Pokemon.Description: The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body.

Pokemon.Name: Lilligant
Pokemon.Description: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokemon is popular with celebrities.

Pokemon.Name: Basculin
Pokemon.Description: Red and blue Basculin get along so poorly, they'll start fighting instantly. These Pokemon are very hostile.

Pokemon.Name: Sandile
Pokemon.Description: They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.

Pokemon.Name: Krokorok
Pokemon.Description: They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.

Pokemon.Name: Krookodile
Pokemon.Description: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

Pokemon.Name: Darumaka
Pokemon.Description: When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.

Pokemon.Name: Darmanitan
Pokemon.Description: Its internal fire burns at 2,500 F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

Pokemon.Name: Maractus
Pokemon.Description: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokemon that prey on its flower seeds.

Pokemon.Name: Dwebble
Pokemon.Description: This Pokemon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.

Pokemon.Name: Crustle
Pokemon.Description: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

Pokemon.Name: Scraggy
Pokemon.Description: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.

Pokemon.Name: Scrafty
Pokemon.Description: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.

Pokemon.Name: Sigilyph
Pokemon.Description: They never vary the route they fly, because their memories of guarding an ancient city remain steadfast.

Pokemon.Name: Yamask
Pokemon.Description: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

Pokemon.Name: Cofagrigus
Pokemon.Description: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.

Pokemon.Name: Tirtouga
Pokemon.Description: Restored from a fossil, this Pokemon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.

Pokemon.Name: Carracosta
Pokemon.Description: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.

Pokemon.Name: Archen
Pokemon.Description: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokemon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.

Pokemon.Name: Archeops
Pokemon.Description: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.

Pokemon.Name: Trubbish
Pokemon.Description: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

Pokemon.Name: Garbodor
Pokemon.Description: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.

Pokemon.Name: Zorua
Pokemon.Description: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.

Pokemon.Name: Zoroark
Pokemon.Description: Bonds between these Pokemon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.

Pokemon.Name: Minccino
Pokemon.Description: They greet one another by rubbing each other with their tails, which are always kept well groomed and clean.

Pokemon.Name: Cinccino
Pokemon.Description: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.

Pokemon.Name: Gothita
Pokemon.Description: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

Pokemon.Name: Gothorita
Pokemon.Description: They use hypnosis to control people and Pokemon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.

Pokemon.Name: Gothitelle
Pokemon.Description: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.

Pokemon.Name: Solosis
Pokemon.Description: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

Pokemon.Name: Duosion
Pokemon.Description: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.

Pokemon.Name: Reuniclus
Pokemon.Description: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

Pokemon.Name: Ducklett
Pokemon.Description: These bird Pokemon are excellent divers. They swim around in the water eating their favorite food--peat moss.

Pokemon.Name: Swanna
Pokemon.Description: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

Pokemon.Name: Vanillite
Pokemon.Description: The temperature of their breath is -58 F. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the areas around them.

Pokemon.Name: Vanillish
Pokemon.Description: Snowy mountains are this Pokemon's habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.

Pokemon.Name: Vanilluxe
Pokemon.Description: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and attack their foes with violent blizzards.

Pokemon.Name: Deerling
Pokemon.Description: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

Pokemon.Name: Sawsbuck
Pokemon.Description: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck's horns.

Pokemon.Name: Emolga
Pokemon.Description: The energy made in its cheeks' electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.

Pokemon.Name: Karrablast
Pokemon.Description: These mysterious Pokemon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.

Pokemon.Name: Escavalier
Pokemon.Description: They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. Even when in trouble, they face opponents bravely.

Pokemon.Name: Foongus
Pokemon.Description: It lures people in with its Poke Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poke Ball is unknown.

Pokemon.Name: Amoonguss
Pokemon.Description: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poke Balls, in a swaying motion.

Pokemon.Name: Frillish
Pokemon.Description: With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.

Pokemon.Name: Jellicent
